Arrays, Strings & Pointers – C Programming

## Introduction

This section focuses on three very important concepts in C programming: arrays, strings, and pointers. These topics are essential for handling large amounts of data efficiently and are widely used in data structures, algorithms, and system-level programming.

Arrays help store multiple values of the same type, strings are used to handle text data, and pointers provide direct memory access, making C a powerful low-level language. Mastering these concepts is crucial for becoming strong in C programming.

